Rating: 4
I have made this dish maybe a dozen times. I love it! By far my favorite chix provencal recipe. I never really follow the precise amounts dictated by the recipe, using the amounts of the ingredients I happen to buy or have around, and it has never been less than satisfying and perfectly delicious. I always use the thigh meat, and now that I am no longer afraid of them, I like to double the anchovies. It goes brilliantly with couscous. I've made it for several dinner parties and it has always been a hit. It's ideal if you just let it slow cook in the oven for six hours at a low temp. For dinner parties this is perfect, because then you can attend to other things, knowing that the big dish is pretty much out of the way! And the best part is that you can make a double recipe and then freeze it in batches, and as long as you eat it within six months of freezing it--it somehow manages to get tastier and tastier.

