Rating: 3
I made this with skinless thighs to reduce the amount of fat and served it over wheat pasta. Definitely tasty and easy to make. The recipe was a wee bit salty (read: a LOT bit). I think I added a little too much caper juice, and when combined with the anchovies and olives, it was overwhelming. As a result, the sage and thyme flavors were overpowered. I would add twice the amount of the herbs next time... and there will definitely be a next time. It's a great weekday meal - you can do the dishes/clean the kitchen while the dish is simmering!

