Rating: 4
This was an excellent dish, however I used chicken breasts instead of thighs. I also added a can of chopped artichoke hearts, sliced mushrooms and roasted red bell peppers. To keep the skin from getting soggy, I placed the browned chicken breasts on top of the sauce and baked in a 375 degree oven for one hour uncovered. Towards the end of the cooking time I sprinkled the dish with freshly grated Parmesean cheese. I served this dish with a side of pasta, using the sauce from the chicken to cover it. I also served warm crusty bread and a salad of sliced fresh mozerella with tomato, basil and roasted red pepper strips, topped with an anchovie butter dressing.

